Indonesia.impact:
Banks and Non-bank financial service institutions that have Data Centers and/or Disaster Recovery Centers are required to place Electronic Systems in Data Centers and/or Disaster Recovery Centers in the territory of Indonesia and are required to carry out Information Technology-Based Transaction Processing in the territory of Indonesia. They can place Electronic Systems in Data Centers and/or Disaster Recovery Centers outside Indonesian territrory upon approval by the Indonesian government in a very limited conditions.Specifically, banks and -Bank Financial Services Institution (NBFIs) may place Data Centers and/or Disaster Recovery Centers outside Indonesia subject to OJK approval’s and for the following uses:
●	Electronic Systems used to support integrated analysis in meeting the provisions issued by the Bank's/NBFI’s home country authorities that are global in nature, including cross-country;
●	Electronic Systems used for integrated risk management with the Bank's/NBFI’s head office or parent office or main entity office outside Indonesia;
●	Electronic Systems used for the implementation of anti-money laundering and prevention of terrorism financing in an integrated manner with the Bank's/NBFI’s head office or parent office outside Indonesia;
●	Electronic Systems used for global customer service, which requires integration with the Bank's/NBFI’s group Electronic Systems outside Indonesia;
●	Electronic Systems used for communication management between the Bank's/NBFI’s head office and branch offices, or between subsidiaries and parent companies; and/or
●	Electronic Systems used for internal Bank/NBFI management

In addition for banks, in the event of conditions that significantly disrupt Bank operations, OJK may determine the placement of the Electronic System at a Data Center and/or Disaster Recovery Center outside the territory of Indonesia other than the 6 criteria for a temporary period. The examples of conditions that significantly disrupt the Bank’s operations include, among others, the cessation of services from an IT service provider and the absence of alternative IT service providers within Indonesia capable of delivering similar services. Before the end of the temporary placement period of Electronic Systems at Data Centers and/or Disaster Recovery Centers located outside the territory of Indonesia, Banks shall conduct an evaluation to determine the availability and reliability of Electronic System providers within Indonesia.

Note that the Regulation of the Financial Services Authority (OJK) No.11/POJK.03/2022 on the Implementation of Information Technology by Commercial Banks amended the Regulation of Financial Services Authority No.38/POJK.03/2016.

