Indonesia.impact:
Regarding requirements of restrictions affecting online advertising, the Regulation by OJK concerning advertising in financial services is stipulated through OJK Regulation Number 22 of 2023 on Consumer and Public Protection in the Financial Services Sector which features some regulatory aspects including the obligation for Financial Services Providers (FSPs) to include their name/logo and a statement of being licensed and supervised by OJK in all offers, product summaries, promotions, or advertisements. In relation to the marketing of cryptocurrency products, Cryptocurrency Trading Companies are prohibited from marketing their products through advertisements other than on the official media of the Cryptocurrency Trading Company.

Furthermore, in relation to entities regulated and supervised under Division of Financial Sector Technology Innovation, Digital Financial Assets, and Crypto Assets at the OJK, the marketing communications of Digital Financial Asset products and/or services are specifically governed by Article 124 of OJK Regulation No. 27 of 2024, which stipulates:
1.	In marketing Digital Financial Asset products and/or services, Traders are required to provide information that is accurate, not misleading, and in compliance with prevailing laws and regulations.
2.	The information referred to in paragraph (1) must, at a minimum, meet the following requirements:
a.	Be transparent to Consumers;
b.	Include warnings regarding risks and price volatility;
c.	Not indicate or create the impression that investment in Digital Financial Assets will generate high and guaranteed returns;
d.	Not create assumptions that losses will occur if Digital Financial Assets are not purchased immediately; and
Not suggest the purchase of Digital Financial Assets using any form of debt."

