Mongolia.impact:
Article 3 (Technological safety requirements) of the "Regulation on Technical Requirements for Processing Sensitive, Biometric, and Genetic Data" sets out the requirements for servers processing sensitive personal information. Among other stipulations, it mandates that the server must be physically located within the territory of Mongolia and must be accessible exclusively from within Mongolia.

Specifically, Article 3.2. The data processing server must meet the following requirements:
3.2.1. Be located in the territory of Mongolia;
3.2.2. be accessible only from Mongolia;
3.2.3. The server must be located in a dedicated technical room;
3.2.4. Ability to increase server capacity if necessary;
3.2.5. Ability to exchange information through the "KUR" state information exchange system;
3.2.6. Be connected to the network time server of the Communications Regulatory Commission;
3.2.7. The information exchange system must be protected by an "SSL" certificate; 
3.2.8. Regularly back up information systems. 
Moreover, Section 3.3. The data processor shall have a firewall system that regularly monitors incoming and outgoing network traffic and blocks suspicious activity and access in order to ensure network security.

Pursuant to Article 1, the objective of this Regulation is to establish the principles and technological security requirements governing the processing of sensitive personal data, as well as genetic and biometric data, as stipulated in Articles 9 and 10 of the Law on the Protection of Personal Data.

Article 7.2 of the law mandates that shareholders, the chairperson of the board of directors, members, executive management, review board, and employees of the bank must refrain from disclosing, revealing, or using any information considered confidential by the bank, its customers, or third parties, except in the following circumstances:
- The individual must provide written consent to disclose the Information;
- Disclosure may be made in response to a legitimate request from the authorized official of the Bank of Mongolia, its regulator, or the State Inspector of the Bank of Mongolia;
- If the prosecutor has approved the investigator's proposal upon the request of the management of the court, the prosecutor's organization, or by the requirements of the anti-corruption organization, police organization, or intelligence organization to verify Information related to money laundering and terrorist financing;
- Upon proof of a violation of Mongolian law, a request may be made by an international legal organization or the government of a foreign country with which Mongolia has established an agreement of legal assistance. 
- The Financial Regulatory Commission is empowered to submit requests to foreign countries' competent financial regulatory authority per the obligations outlined in agreements and memoranda of understanding concluded by the Commission for monitoring licensed activities;
- Information must be submitted to the credit database in compliance with legal obligations; 
- Bailiffs requesting Information on a payer's account must obtain approval from the head of the court's enforcement department; 
- The Customs and Tax Department has the authority to demand payment of customs and tax liabilities from specific customers and conduct tax audits as per its legislated functions; 
- Auditors of the Deposit Insurance Corporation may demand Information to exercise their powers as stipulated in the Law on Deposit Insurance in Banks; 
- Information required by tax authorities under international agreements on exchanging Information for tax purposes is specified in Section 18.1.2 of the General Tax Law; 
- The state audit organization has the power to demand Information concerning the implementation of auditing functions as stipulated by law;

