Russian Federation.impact:
Under Russian law, electronic signatures are granted the same legal status as handwritten signatures.

According to Article 4, The principles of using electronic signatures are as follows:

1. The right of participants in electronic interactions to use any type of electronic signature at their discretion, unless the use of a specific type of electronic signature is required by federal laws, regulatory legal acts adopted in accordance with them, or by agreement between the participants in the electronic interaction;

2. The ability of participants in electronic interactions to use, at their discretion, any information technology and/or technical means that enable them to meet the requirements of this Federal Law in relation to the use of specific types of electronic signatures;

3. The inadmissibility of denying the legal force of an electronic signature and/or an electronic document signed with it solely on the grounds that the electronic signature was not created by hand but by means of an electronic signature tool used for the automatic creation and/or verification of electronic signatures within an information system.

