Thailand.impact:
Thailand does not implement requirements to surrender patents, source code, software in order to win tender. The requirements for surrendering source code, encryption, and other trade secrets are not imposed. It depends on an agreement, which is normally specified in terms of requirements initially, between a procuring entity and a supplier.

To determine the price and minimum requirement for Computer programs and appliances. The procuring entity are required to use the price as focal price according to the Article 4 of the Public Procurement and Supplies Administration Act B.E.2560 which stipulates that “focal price” means the price used as a basis for comparing prices offered by persons tendering proposals, in respect of which procurement may actually be materialized in the following orders:
(1) the price derived from the calculation in accordance with the rules prescribed by the Focal Prices Committee;
(2) the price derived from the supplies index-price database established by the Comptroller-General’s Department;
(3) the standard price prescribed by the Bureau of the Budget or other central agencies;

In the case where there exists the price under (1), the price under (1) shall first be adopted. In the case where the price under (1) does not exist but there exists the price under (2) or (3), the price under (2) or (3) shall first be adopted, provided that in considering whether the price under (2) or (3) shall be adopted, prime regard shall be had to the interest of the State agency.

The Guidelines for the Procurement of Computer Programs by the Department of Intellectual Property (DIP) under the Ministry of Commerce, states that for the procurement of computer programs the software must strictly follow the Public Procurement and Supplies Administration Act (Section 54-68 Chapter 6) and the Regulation of the Ministry of Finance on Public Procurement and Supplies Administration (Clause 21-91 Part 2: Procurement Process Chapter 2). Specifically, computer programs software refer to Source Code, Application Software, Utility Software, Software Package, Open-source Software, Freeware, Shareware, Operating system: Microsoft Windows, macOS, Unix, DOS Linux, iOS, and Android, Subscription-based Software, and Commercial Software. The Ministry of Digital Economy and Society empowers to determine the focal price and the qualifications of Computer Programs which other government departments require to follow.

