Thailand.impact:
The Budget Procedures Act provides that the foreigner is not allowed to acquire shares exceeding 50 percent in publicly controlled firms or state-owned enterprises (SOEs). 

Section 4 provides that “State enterprise” means: 
(1) a Government organisation under the law on the establishment of Government organisations, a State undertaking established by law or a State-owned business entity;
(2) a limited company or public limited company of which more than fifty percent of the capital is contributed by a Government agency or a State enterprise under (1);
(3) a limited company or public limited company of which more than fifty percent of the capital is contributed by a Government agency and a State enterprise under (1) or (2), or by State enterprises under (1) and (2), or by a State enterprise under (2).

