Thailand.impact:
Broadcasting and Television Business Act B.E.2551 states that any person who operates a television business and sound broadcasting business must obtain a license from the National Broadcasting and Telecommunications Commission (NBTC) (Section 7). There are three types of broadcasting license for radio and television program, including (Section 10):
(1) Type 1: public services business, available only to government entities, charities, and educational institutions (not allow private sector operators);
(2) Type 2: community services (not allow private sector operators);
(3) Type3: profit-making at national, regional, or local levels.

The criteria in setting up the qualifications of the applicant shall be as follows, such as shall not be a bankrupt, applicant shall never have a telecommunications business license revoked, or directors, managers or persons in authority of the applicant shall not be a person sentenced by a final judgment for an offence committed under this Act (Section 8). The license applies to news provider, television and sound broadcasting business (TV program or radio), digital TV.

Online service providers are not required to apply for a broadcasting or television operation license from the NBTC of Thailand. According to the Act on the Organization to Assign Radio Frequency and to Regulate the Broadcasting and Telecommunications Services B.E. 2553 (Section 4) and Broadcasting and Television Business Act B.E.2551 (Section 4), sound broadcasting and television services are limited to services that provide public news or programs for reception via receiving apparatus, whether by radio frequency, wire, optical, electromagnetic, or any other system or combination thereof, or other similar services prescribed by the NBTC.

