Thailand.impact:
The Electronic Transaction Act (No.4) 2019 introduces the Digital Identification or Digital Identity Verification. The law grants the power to Digital Economy and Society Minister (MDES) and the Committee to set up rules and requirements regarding digital authentication and supervise the digital ID platform. The business service related to digital identity verification that deals with the electronic transaction must obtain the license (Section 34/4). The business operator who fails to comply with such requirement or operates unauthorized digital authentication business shall be liable to fine, imprisonment, or both (Section. 45/1). 

In particular, Royal Decree on Supervision of Service Businesses Relating to Digital Identification and Authentication Systems that Are Subject to Licensing B.E.2565  issued under the Electronic Transactions Act aims to establish a regulatory framework for digital identification and authentication services by setting out clear licensing requirements, eligibility criteria, and operational obligations. It ensures that such services are trustworthy, secure, and reliable, thereby fostering confidence in electronic transactions.

Under this Royal Decree, services related to digital identification and authentication systems are required to obtain a license before commencing operations, as outlined in Section 7. Exemptions from the licensing requirement are specified in Section 8.
Section 7. The provision of a service relating to digital identification and authentication that possesses any of the following characteristics shall be a service that is subject to licensing:
(1) an identity proofing service;
(2) an authenticator lifecycle management service;
(3) an authentication service;
(4) a service for exchanging data for digital identification and authentication that is a network or system which connects and exchanges data relating to digital identification and authentication, excluding a service of an intermediary.

Section 8. The provision of any of the following services relating to digital identification and authentication systems shall be exempt from obtaining a license:
(1) an identification and authentication service operated by a service provider issuing a certificate for supporting electronic signatures, in order to support the use of electronic signatures under the law on electronic transactions;
(2) an identification and authentication service used by a person for his or her internal businesses without providing the service to external parties;
(3) a service relating to digital identification and authentication systems in businesses prescribed by the Notification of the Commission.

